scRNAseq data analysis CRISPR Screening BM: Filtering low quality cells and genes - QC and doublet removal

Researcher: LuÃ­s Galan

Author: Eric Canton - MarÃ­a Maqueda

13th August 2024

Scope

This document aims to filter out poor quality cells and genes. This is an standard first QC step for the scRNAseq data pre-processing analysis. Commonly used QC metrics include the exploration of number of unique genes detected in each cell or the percentage of reads that map to the mitochondrial genome.

Primary data

A total of two samples (Bone Marrow) were library-prepared and sequenced by CRG Sequencing platform at PRBB. Libraries were prepared using 10x Single Cell 3âv3 kit. Corresponding biological samples were delivered to the sequencing platform in Decemberâ24 and sequencing data was received in Februaryâ24. Each sample corresponds to a different condition:

  • CD45+ cells at 4.5 months (CD45_4_5)
  • CD45+ cells transplanted from KDR+ progenitors at 4.5 months (CD45_BFP_4_5) activated from 7* specific genes identified by CRISPRa in an earlier project phase.

*Genes related to HSC development fate.

Methods

Following criteria is applied:

  • Cells with mitochondrial content higher than 12% are discarded.
  • Cells with less than 500 counts are discarded.
  • Cells with more than 10k genes or less than 300 genes are discarded.

Ribosomal genes are removed from the dataset. Additionally, those genes expressed in 5 or less cells (among all samples) are also discarded.

QC is performed by means of Seurat R package (Hao et al. 2023) (v5.0.0).

REMARKS: (a) Applied criteria is quite permissive since, in general, it is expected to conduct a second round of QC (b) Cells classified as doublets/multiplets per sample, identified in a previous analysis, will be also inspected.

Results

All scRNAseq data samples were merged into a Seurat object

## An object of class Seurat 
## 32285 features across 14096 samples within 1 assay 
## Active assay: RNA (32285 features, 0 variable features)
##  2 layers present: counts.CD45_4_5.1, counts.CD45_BFP_4_5.2

The complete dataset, without any filtering applied, includes a total of 32285 features (genes) over 14096 samples (cells) distributed in the three samples.

Doublets removal

Doublets will not be discarded at this point. Their assessment will be conducted in next analysis phase.

Number of cells per sample: initially and after doublets removal
Sample.ID Initial.Cells Cells.woDBL
CD45_4_5 8461 7641
CD45_BFP_4_5 5635 5294

QC metrics

Exploration

Prior to apply any QC filtering, first a general exploration is conducted to assess the overall cells quality. This includes, per barcode (cell):

  • Number of genes
  • Number of counts
  • Mitochondrial content
  • Ribosomal content

Alternatively, a joint plot between metrics is also of interest to check relationships among variables.

All samples behave roughly equally independently of their condition.

Subset low quality cells

Cells are subset based on above mentioned QC criteria. The final number of cells is shown in the following table.

Number of cells per sample: initially, after doublets removal and after final QC criteria
Sample.ID Initial.Cells Cells.woDBL Cells.FINAL
CD45_4_5 8461 7641 7510
CD45_BFP_4_5 5635 5294 5020

After filtering, QC plots are again visualized:

Discard non-expressed and ribosomal genes

Finally, those genes that are expressed in less than 5 (considering all samples together) will be discarded. The number of cells expressing a particular gene, per sample, is computed:

Example of number of cells expressing a particular gene (in rows) per sample (columns)
counts.CD45_4_5 counts.CD45_BFP_4_5
Xkr4 46 25
Gm1992 0 1
Gm19938 0 0
Gm37381 0 0
Rp1 11 3
Sox17 0 0
Gm37587 0 0
Gm37323 0 0
Mrpl15 1232 931
Lypla1 1374 916

As a reminder, a total of 32285 genes were initially included in the expression matrix (for all samples). Out of those, 17837 are kept for downstream analysis, after discarding the non-expressed ones (or just residual).

Finally, ribosomal genes are removed from this dataset. The number of present ribosomal genes are 96 genes.

The final dataset includes a total of 17741 features (genes) over 12530 cells distributed in two conditions. Doublet cells have been removed.
